msgctxt "156_Affluent Old Man"
msgid ""
"Did you change your mind? I know it must be hard\r\n"
"to just walk away from three million yen."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "168_Affluent Old Man"
msgid "Hello, young man. I notice you've been making some excellent plays."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "180_Tanimura"
msgid "Uh... I guess. You need something, old-timer?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "192_Affluent Old Man"
msgid ""
"Now, now... Don't disregard me as some addled old fogey.\r\n"
"I've been watching you, and I know a daredevil when I see\r\n"
"one. Nothing like the rush of winning the jackpot, right?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "204_Tanimura"
msgid "......"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "216_Affluent Old Man"
msgid ""
"Let me get to the point. I happen to know a place where you\r\n"
"can make some real moneyÔºçmuch more than you could ever\r\n"
"scrounge up at a tame little venue like this. Interested?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "228_Tanimura"
msgid ""
"I dunno... That's pretty much the opening line of every\r\n"
"sketchy deal in the book. Besides, do I look like I need money?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "240_Affluent Old Man"
msgid ""
"Yes. Yes, you do. And believe me, a man of my means would\r\n"
"know. You definitely need the money. Maybe you even deserve it. But alas, "
"I'm beginning to ramble..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "252_Affluent Old Man"
msgid ""
"So let me give it to you straight: my game can earn you\r\n"
"three million yen in one go. That pique your interest? I'll\r\n"
"say it again, making tiny bets here will get you nowhere."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "264_Tanimura"
msgid ""
"(Three million yen for one game? Yeah, that's gotta be a scam. But, at the "
"same time, I am kinda curious to see where this goes...)"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "276_Tanimura"
msgid "So I can really make three million, huh?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "288_Affluent Old Man"
msgid ""
"Hahaha. Yes, that's right. I wouldn't lie.\r\n"
"Three million yen for one game."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "300_Affluent Old Man"
msgid ""
"You may be young, but I like your spirit.\r\n"
"That's why I decided to give you this opportunity."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "312_Affluent Old Man"
msgid ""
"But if you're not interested, just say so.\r\n"
"Now what's it going to be?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "324_Tanimura"
msgid "(I'm still not convinced. What should I say to this guy?)"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "336_Tanimura"
msgid "Sorry, but I'm gonna have to pass on this one."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "348_Affluent Old Man"
msgid ""
"Hahaha, even with three million yen on the line?\r\n"
"Certainly you overlook the magnitude of this offer..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "360_Affluent Old Man"
msgid ""
"Lucky for you, I've got some time on my hands right now.\r\n"
"I'll be enjoying the lounge here for a while, so if you do\r\n"
"change your mind, you know where to find me."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "372_Tanimura"
msgid "All right, I'm in."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "384_Affluent Old Man"
msgid ""
"Excellent. Then come with me. The game takes place\r\n"
"a little ways from here. Can you spare the time?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "396_Tanimura"
msgid "As long as you spare the change."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "432_Tanimura"
msgid ""
"Sorry, but I'm not interested.\r\n"
"Why don't you ask somebody else?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "444_Affluent Old Man"
msgid ""
"I see... I may just do that. But you're wasting a good opportunity, you "
"know."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "456_Tanimura"
msgid "(As they say, discretion is the better part of valor.)"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "468_Affluent Old Man"
msgid "Hear Him Out"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "480_Affluent Old Man"
msgid "Ignore Him"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "492_Affluent Old Man"
msgid "I'm in."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "504_Affluent Old Man"
msgid "I'll pass."
msgstr ""